  <main class="wrap">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div class="date">Last updated: February 5, 2026</div>

    <p>Dog Days is a dog care tracking app that lets you log meals, walks, pupdates, and share a Pack with others.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account information:</strong> email address, user ID</li>
      <li><strong>Pack data:</strong> pack name, dog name, member roles</li>
      <li><strong>Content you add:</strong> logs, pupdates, photos, notes</li>
      <li><strong>Device data:</strong> push notification tokens</li>
      <li><strong>Usage analytics:</strong> basic app events (e.g., sign up, log created)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To create and manage your account</li>
      <li>To sync pack data across members</li>
      <li>To send optional notifications</li>
      <li>To understand app usage and improve features</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your data. We only share information with service providers required to run the app:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Firebase (Google)</strong> for authentication, database, file storage, and analytics</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your Choices</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You can delete logs, pupdates, and your account at any time in the app</li>
      <li>You can leave or delete a Pack (if eligible)</li>
      <li>You can turn off notifications</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>Data is retained until you delete it or your account is deleted.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions? Email <a href="mailto:support@dog-days.com">support@dog-days.com</a>.</p>
  </main>
